Adam Johnson was charged with three offences of sexual activity with a child on Thursday . 
  Sunderland winger has not been suspended by the club despite the charges . 
  Dick Advocaat has confirmed Johnson is available for selection against Stoke on Saturday . 
  Johnson will appear at Peterlee Magistrates Court on May 20 . 
  The 27-year-old has been used as a substitute in the last three games . 
 